You have been given an integer N as input . your task is to write a
program to print N rows of Floyadâ€™s Triangle. Floyd's pattern is a rightangled triangular array of natural numbers , used for the numbering of
lines in a printout
.
For N=4,
1
23
456
78910
Answer ---------
import java.util.Scanner;
public class  FloydsTriangle{
    public static void main(String args[]){
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    int n = sc.nextInt();
    
    int counter=1;
    
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) { // Outer loop for rows
            for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++){
            System.out.print(counter +" ");
            counter++;
        }
        System.out.println();
    }
}
    
}
